    correct: 3,
    explanation: "<strong>Key Clues in the Passage</strong><br>One study found no \"enduring increases,\" while another found a significant increase \"in the three years following liberalization.\" Together, that points to a short-term rise, not a permanent one.<br><br><strong>Working Through Each Choice:</strong><br><strong>(A)</strong> ✗ The passage does not compare consistency with non-liberalizing countries. <em>(Out of scope)</em><br><strong>(B)</strong> ✗ Henry found gains within three years, not only after three years. <em>(Misreads passage)</em><br><strong>(C)</strong> ✗ No information is given about prior economist expectations. <em>(No textual support)</em><br><strong>(D)</strong> ✓ This captures the temporary post-liberalization increase followed by lack of enduring effects.<br><br><strong>Correct Answer: D</strong><br>This question tests synthesis across studies: reconcile apparent disagreement by inferring a time-limited effect."
