    explanation: "<strong>Key Clues in the Passage</strong><br>Current preservation efforts focus on spoken language, yet \"some expressions...appear only in songs.\" To preserve a \"comprehensive range\" of information, songs must be preserved too.<br><br><strong>Working Through Each Choice:</strong><br><strong>(A)</strong> ✗ The issue is preservation scope, not the percentage of song phrases from speech. <em>(Out of scope)</em><br><strong>(B)</strong> ✗ Comparing musical style across groups does not address safeguarding language expressions. <em>(No textual support)</em><br><strong>(C)</strong> ✓ This directly fixes the identified gap in preservation practice.<br><strong>(D)</strong> ✗ The passage does not compare ecological expressions against all other information types. <em>(Unsupported comparison)</em><br><br><strong>Correct Answer: C</strong><br>This tests means-end reasoning: identify the concrete action needed to satisfy the stated goal."
