    correct: 1,
    explanation: "<strong>Key Clues in the Passage</strong><br>The passage says Heartburn has autobiographical parallels yet is \"largely pure invention.\" Ignoring that balance and forcing additional real-life matches leads to unsupported biographical claims.<br><br><strong>Working Through Each Choice:</strong><br><strong>(A)</strong> ✗ Influence from earlier writers is never part of the discussion. <em>(Out of scope)</em><br><strong>(B)</strong> ✓ This directly captures the risk of overextending autobiography beyond evidence.<br><strong>(C)</strong> ✗ Readership size is unrelated to the biography-versus-invention issue. <em>(No textual support)</em><br><strong>(D)</strong> ✗ Such readers overstate real-life links, not minimize them. <em>(Reverses the logic)</em><br><br><strong>Correct Answer: B</strong><br>This tests careful boundary-setting between factual inspiration and fictional construction."
