    explanation: "<strong>Key Clues in the Passage</strong><br>Biophilic design uses \"organic or biomorphic forms and textures\" to connect architecture with nature and human biology. Curves fit because they visually echo natural shapes.<br><br><strong>Working Through Each Choice:</strong><br><strong>(A)</strong> ✗ Cultural prevalence does not explain the biophilic rationale given. <em>(Out of scope)</em><br><strong>(B)</strong> ✗ Biophilic design seeks coherence with nature, not distinction from it. <em>(Contradicts passage)</em><br><strong>(C)</strong> ✓ This matches the biomorphic principle described in the text.<br><strong>(D)</strong> ✗ The sentence concerns nature-linked form logic, not practicality-versus-taste tradeoffs. <em>(No textual support)</em><br><br><strong>Correct Answer: C</strong><br>This tests concept application: connect a design principle (biophilia) to a specific formal choice (curves)."
