    passage: "In a recent study, Antonia Olivia Dolan and colleagues investigated the relationship between people's music preferences and their preferred listening volume. Participants listened to recordings—Beyoncé's \"Crazy in Love,\" Led Zeppelin's \"Whole Lotta Love,\" and others—at their preferred volume and indicated their most and least favorite among the recordings. The researchers found that participants listened to recordings they liked most at a higher volume than recordings they liked least. And given that the frequencies in all the recordings were within the audible range of these participants (all of whom had clinically typical hearing), it is therefore likely that for a given participant, the _____________",
